{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GPAVTK9Px9aYjv7QAKVGeS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The project has a basic skeleton set up. The user's message is the task list from CLAUDE.md. Let me understand what needs to be done:\n\nPhase 1 foundations - the first tasks are:\n1. Project is already initialized (Tauri 2 + Svelte 5 + TailwindCSS 4) ✓\n2. SQLite schema needs to be expanded (missing tables: transaction_splits, recurring_transactions, import_batches, tags, transaction_tags, categorization_rules, and missing columns like currency, fitid, import_batch_id)\n3. Implement Tauri Rust commands (CRUD accounts, transactions)\n\n\n4. Import OFX/QIF/CSV\n5. Layout principal with sidebar\n6. Transaction list\n7. Budget categories CRUD\n8. Budget mensuel\n9. Vue budget\n\nThis is a massive undertaking. I need to work through this systematically, starting with the database schema migration to add all the missing tables and columns, then build out the Rust commands, frontend types, and UI components. My priority is getting the schema right first, then the sidebar layout, TypeScript types, and database store before tackling the accounts and transaction features.\n\nActually, I realize with `tauri-plugin-sql` the frontend can call SQL directly through `execute()` and `select()` methods, so I don't need Rust commands for basic CRUD operations—only for complex things like imports. This simplifies the architecture significantly. I'll start by updating the database migration with all the required tables, then create the TypeScript types, build the database utility layer, construct the sidebar layout, and work through the accounts, transactions, and budget pages in sequence.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4237,"cache_read_input_tokens":25076,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4237}